      "source": [
        "**Definition.**\n",
        "- `players.shape` is an *attribute* since it gives stored information and uses no parentheses.\n",
        "- `players.mean()` is a *method* since it is an action and uses parentheses."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "79ef9d54",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "79ef9d54"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print('a function approach: ', len(height_in_array))\n",
        "print('using a attribute: ', height_in_array.size)\n",
        "\n",
        "# vs. an action\n",
        "print('using a method: ', height_in_array.mean())\n",
        "\n",
        "# methods can be stacked!\n",
        "print('using another method: ', height_in_array.mean().round(2))\n"
      ]
    },
